#vanilla-ui-ui

    h3.section-header Vanilla UI Plus

    //-
        Vanilla UI Plus
        Updated 2019-03-22
    //-
    +modCard('vanilla-ui-plus', 'Vanilla UI Plus', 'https://www.moddb.com/mods/vanilla-ui-plus/downloads', 'fnv-color')
        +author Axonis
        +version 7.71
        +installation Install #[span.file Vanilla UI Plus (New Vegas) 7.71]
        +notes
            | Vanilla UI Plus (VUI+) is a Fallout 3 and New Vegas mod that greatly improves the user interface without
            | compromising the original style.

    #california-fonts
        +name('CALIFORNIA Fonts for Vanilla', 'https://www.nexusmods.com/newvegas/mods/66000', 'fnv')
        +modInfo
            +author emptybell
            +version 0.7
            +installation Install #[+file('CALIFORNIA Fonts for Vanilla')]
            +notes More ‘modern’, smaller fonts for VUI+, since the text size seems to be the biggest attraction of DarnUI

    //-
        Vanilla HUD Remastered
        Updated 2019-03-22
    //-
    +modCard('vanilla-hud-remastered', 'Vanilla HUD Remastered', 'https://www.nexusmods.com/newvegas/mods/64102', 'fnv-color')
        +author BmanBlazer
        +version 1.83
        +installation Install #[span.file Vanilla HUD Remastered 4K v1.83]
        +instructions
            | Select VHR with VUI+ Patch.
        +notes
            | This mod is designed to update the HUD for 1080p resolutions or higher (1440p, 4K, etc) while maintaining the
            | same original look and style.

    #vanilla-hud-remastered-patch
        +name('Vanilla HUD Remastered Patch', 'https://www.moddb.com/mods/vanilla-ui-plus/addons/vanilla-hud-remastered-patch', 'fnv')
        +modInfo
            +author Axonis
            +version 1.83c
            +installation Install #[+file('Vanilla HUD Remastered Patch 1.83c')]
            +notes
                | Patches Vanilla HUD Remastered 1.83 to retain compatibility with the latest VUI+
                | features. To install, allow VHR to overwrite VUI+, and allow this patch to overwrite VHR.

